{{infobox biodatabase |title = KiSAO |logo = [[File:KiSAO logo.svg|frameless]] |description = An ontology providing support in unambiguously referring to simulation algorithms when describing a simulation experiment. |scope = simulation algorithms, their characteristics and parameters |organism = |center = [[European Bioinformatics Institute|EMBL-EBI]] |laboratory = |author = |pmid = 22027554 |released = |standard = [[MIRIAM]] |format = [[Web Ontology Language|OWL]] |url = [http://biomodels.net/kisao/ KiSAO home page], [http://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/KISAO KiSAO at BioPortal] |download = [http://biomodels.net/kisao/#kisaoDownload KiSAO home page] |webservice = |sql = |sparql = |webapp = |standalone = [http://biomodels.net/kisao/libkisao.html libKiSAO, a java library to query KiSAO] |license = [[Artistic License|Artistic Licence]] |version = 2.3.5 (April 2014) |versioning = |frequency = |curation = yes (manual) |bookmark = yes }}
The '''Kinetic Simulation Algorithm Ontology''' (KiSAO) supplies information about existing algorithms available for the simulation of [[systems biology]] models, their characterization and interrelationships. KiSAO is part of the [[BioModels.net]] project and of the [[COMBINE]] initiative.<ref name="10.1038/msb.2011.77" />
==Structure== KiSAO consists of three main branches: * simulation algorithm, * simulation algorithm characteristic, * simulation algorithm parameter. The elements of each algorithm branch are linked to characteristic and parameter branches using ''has characteristic'' and ''has parameter'' relationships accordingly.The algorithm branch itself is hierarchically structured using ''subClassOf'' relationships, which denote that the descendant algorithms were derived from, or specify, more general ancestors.
