'''Urs Schreiber''' (born 1974) is a mathematician specializing in the connection between mathematics and theoretical physics (especially [[string theory]]) and currently working as a researcher at the [[Czech Academy of Sciences]], Institute of Mathematics, Department for Algebra, Geometry and Mathematical Physics.<ref>[http://www.math.cas.cz/annuaire/membres_perman.php?membre=perm Researchers], [[Czech Academy of Sciences]], retrieved 2015-07-31.</ref>
==Education== Schreiber obtained his doctorate from the [[University of Duisburg-Essen]] in 2005 with a thesis supervised by [[Robert Graham (physicist)|Robert Graham]] and titled ''From Loop Space Mechanics to Nonabelian Strings''.<ref>[https://duepublico.uni-duisburg-essen.de/servlets/DerivateServlet/Derivate-13658/SchreiberDiss.pdf DuEPublico]</ref>
==Work== Schreiber's research fields include the [[mathematical foundation of quantum field theory]].
Schreiber is a co-creator of the [[nLab|''n''Lab]], a [[wiki]] for research mathematicians and physicists working in [[higher category theory]].
== Selected writings == *With Hisham Sati, ''[http://ncatlab.org/schreiber/show/Mathematical+Foundations+of+Quantum+Field+and+Perturbative+String+Theory Mathematical Foundations of Quantum Field and Perturbative String Theory]'', Proceedings of Symposia in Pure Mathematics, volume 83 AMS (2011) *{{cite arXiv |last=Schreiber |first=Urs |eprint=1310.7930v1 |title = Differential cohomology in a cohesive ∞-topos|year=2013 |version= |class=math-ph }}
